{
  "name": "on-computers-tips-is-sun-s-sparc-archite-65b3b9",
  "title": "Is Sun's SPARC Architecture on Life Support?",
  "description": "Kastner blog post on OnComputersTips observing Sun's long-hyped Rock chip is apparently dead and that \u2014 with the pending Oracle-Sun merger and Solaris already on X64 commodity servers \u2014 the case for SPARC is gone. Kastner muses that Oracle has the opportunity to create a one-stop IT shop with the full hardware-to-application stack, unmatched since IBM exited the application software business 40 years earlier.",
